1 AN ACT exempting the state of Kansas from daylight saving time;
2 providing for moving to permanent daylight saving time upon an act of
3 Congress requiring such move.
4
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
6 Section 1. (a) Commencing after 2 o'clock antemeridian on the first
7 Sunday of November of 2025 following the effective date of this act, the
8 state of Kansas shall not observe daylight saving time and shall be exempt
9 from the daylight saving time provisions of 15 U.S.C. § 260a(a).
10 (b) This section shall not affect the standard time established by
11 United States law governing the movements of common carriers engaged
12 in interstate commerce.
13 (c) This section shall not affect the following times as may be
14 established by a statute, order, rule or regulation of the United States or an
15 agency thereof:
16 (1) The time for performance of an act by an officer or department of
17 the United States;
18 (2) the time within which any rights shall accrue or determine; or
19 (3) the time within which any act shall or shall not be performed by
20 any person subject to the jurisdiction of the United States.
21 (d) This section shall have no force and effect from and after the date
22 of publication in the Kansas register of the notice prescribed in section 2 3,
23 and amendments thereto.
24 Sec. 2. The secretary of state shall monitor the enactment of any
25 law by the state of Missouri that provides that such state shall be exempt
26 from the daylight saving time provisions of 15 U.S.C. § 260a(a). If such
27 law is enacted, the secretary shall cause a notice of such enactment to be
28 published in the Kansas register at the time of the next regular
29 publication of the Kansas register following the date such law becomes
30 effective.
31 Sec. 2. 3. (a) The secretary of state shall monitor the enactment of any
32 federal law that requires the year-round observation of central daylight
33 saving time. If such law is enacted, the secretary shall cause a notice of
34 such enactment to be published in the Kansas register at the time of the
35 next regular publication of the Kansas register following the date such law
36 becomes effective.

